==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corporeity
<hw>Cor`po*re"i*ty</hw> <pr>(k?r`p?-r?"?-t?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[LL. <ets>corporeitas</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>corpor<?/it<?/</ets>.]</ety> <def>The state of having a body; the
state of being corporeal; materiality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The one attributed <qex>corporeity</qex> to God.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Stillingfleet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those who deny light to be matter, do not therefore deny its
<qex>corporeity</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corporify</ent>⟦br⟧
